<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-04-12T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-04-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="815" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d815">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 741.8215/44.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Ambassador to Great
                                    Britain</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-04-12">
                                    <hi rend="italic">April 12, 1912</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Replying to my request for leniency in dealing with the Liberian boundary
                            troubles, the Foreign Office has assured me that the British Government
                            will exercise all possible forbearance. The Governor of Sierra Leone has
                            been instructed to suspend action until he receives further
                            instructions.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Reid.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>